-- OTP Gains as Hungary Manufacturing PMI Rises to Highest in Year
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-04-02T07:33:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-02/otp-gains-as-hungary-manufacturing-pmi-rises-to-highest-in-year.html
OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP) , Hungary’s largest
lender, headed for the strongest level in almost a week, as the
country’s manufacturing confidence index rose to the highest in
a year in March.  The shares advanced 0.7 percent to 3,857 forint at 9:26
a.m. in Budapest. A close at that level would be the highest
since March 27.  Hungary’s purchasing managers’ index rose to 56.8 points in
March from a revised 51.2 points in the previous month, the
Hungarian company MLBKT said in a report today based on
seasonally adjusted data. That’s the highest since February
2011.  European stocks rose after a purchasing managers’ index in
 China  rose to a one-year high in March.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
